ia:\n\nComment: Communists and pro-Communists holding official positions in the Guatemalan government have consistently been pressing for the re-establishment of relations with Czechoslovakia, which were broken in 1948. The renewal of relations may result in an increase of trade between the two countries.\n\nThe Guatemalan government may also hope to obtain military equipment from Czechoslovakia in view of the United States ban on export of arms to Guatemala.\n\nThe new minister also will represent his country in Mexico and will maintain residence there", "token_count": 90, "token_end_0based": 89, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "latin america 6 guatemala renews relations with czechoslovakia comment communists and pro-communists holding official positions in the guatemalan government have consistently been pressing for the re-establishment of relations with czechoslovakia which were broken in 1948 the renewal of relations may result in an increase of trade between the two countries the guatemalan government may also hope to obtain military equipment from czechoslovakia in view of the united states ban on export of arms to guatemala the new minister also will represent his country in mexico and will maintain residence there", "unred_source_page": 6}
